And on this note. If anyone would like to commission an artist. Please ask for examples. I do traditional artwork. Pencil sketch to ink. Can do full color too. And pricing is based off of how long it would take me to finish it, lol.

Work places need to take our mental illness seriously. So long as they take us serious, take us at our word on how we work best, and ALLOW us to do so, we are some of the most productive people on the planet. And by locking us in place, you are wasting talent.

And most of these jobs all advertise room to advance. But never have openings? And if they do, they go to ass kissers. Not those of us with the work knowledge to train/supervise newer employees. Who NEED the change in job to stay sane and NOT walk out your door.

But most jobs treat us very differently than that. Most treat us as broken for eventually getting bored or burned out. "Why can't you just robot up like everyone else!?". 🙄 << My phone suggested this emoji. It's too smart... Anyways!

I grabbed product off the shelves to my cart. Brought it back to my station. Bagged it onto another cart. Someone took that away periodically. I was allowed my own music, used a bt speaker playing Babymetal an Tool. As well some anime opening/ending themes, lol.

I liked my last job because they said they were totally willing to train me doing other things if I got bored dping what I was doing. They liked me. They knew I had ADHD. And I did excellent work! What I did worked perfectly with my meds tbh.

And to have NT's try to throw it in your face that being a jack of all trades is worthless... Why? Because you don't know the full saying? Sounds like a you problem.

"A jack of all trades is a master of none, but oftentimes better than a master of one"

And when it comes to learning new skills. People with ADHD do NOT lie when we put on the resume "willing to learn new skills". Not like most plebs put it there thinking it looks good. You make those of us willing to ACTUALLY do it look like liars because you aren't willing to.

But it is a teachable skill. And I know how to teach people to listen for certain types of people. How to handle them and de-escalate etc. Have any of the call centers I worked for last understood this when applying for supervisor and training spots? No. They laughed at me.

Reading the tone and pitch of people's voices is absolutely 100% a skill. And not one everyone has. Many with ADHD have these skills as a matter of life and death. We have to be able to determine who among the crowd is going to be an asshole to us after all.

But as a professional person, I have worked in call centers on the phones for over 15 years easy. 10k hours? A LONG time ago. I know the right level of attitude to push and when. And I know which customers are going to be a prob the min they start in.

More often than not, I have literally learned new techniques, how to do things I didn't before, or extensively read on a topic. And many with ADHD can relate to this I think. I have been laughed at when I say I'm an master in customer service. And I get it.

One thing about my ADHD, is that I am constantly rethinking past situations, thinking about future interactions, and how to navigate them better. More fake convos than real ones, we all know that drill. Part of this comes with learning new information to better approach things.

The thing that pisses me off a LOT about my ADHD and interacting with others, is not being believed. Or treated like I can't possible be knowledgeable on so many things...

A Thread.

It wouldn't matter the wording either. I could use paranoid, feels off, I could just ask her what's going on because she'd be acting off. I'm accusing her of cheating. Which always would lead to her saying that I "always accuse her of cheating".

I don't even know when she started to plan her exit. How long she's been feeding lies to those she can't avoid. She never let it on to me. And if I ever expressed things felt off, I was accused of "accusing her" of cheating, and how dare I do that to her!

She brought that into the relationship. And it was NEVER my job to be the one to heal it. And it's so telling to me, that as soon as I started to work on better managing my ADHD, she started to really become bitter. Because all the focus was no longer on her disability...

She tells me that my outbursts cause her to feel as if she needs to walk on eggshells around me, or that I'm going to hurt her. Because of her "past trauma, and I'm triggering it." Except that is BS. Her "past" experiences before are not my fault!

This is also a person who I've barely got to hang out with since I moved here. Even during the time that he lived here in N Idaho also! Because he used to be married to her friend, who I met her through to begin with.

He said,
You get mad at the thing, you get loud at it, maybe swear at it. You then quickly calm down, apologize and assure anyone around that it has nothing to do with them. And everyone moves on.
🤔
But I wasn't like this when we first met? I've known him longer baby.

And when I explain this very thing, she responds in all seriousness that I was not like this when we first got together. Which is BS! I asked my best friend from HS to describe what happens when frustrated
He described my outburst to the "T".

She's made it clear that she wanted me to stop those outbursts from EVER happening, and because they still happen I don't care
And because has never listened to me on how to handle the situation, she turns every one into a fight. And turns it on me, saying I'm angry all the time

And rather than ignore, exit, or attempt to sooth me. She instead is angry at me for something that I obviously had no control over. IF I DID, IT WOULDN'T HAPPEN! And 9 out of 10 times, it doesn't. But the math matters nothing to her.

She constantly gets angry at me having an outburst due to my ADHD... No matter the years explaining that this is the same as telling the screaming lunatic "YOU NEED TO CALM DOWN". Explained that she is bringing herself into a situation that has nothing to do with her.
And I have felt like a complete burden for years. I felt like I wasn't providing enough. I felt like I wasn't doing enough to make her happy. I thought I was the problem.

And there have been signs. There more I think back. Coworkers. Would say the same things! SAME EFFING THINGS OVER AND OVER! "Why do you do that?" "That's controlling of her." "There needs to be a level of forgive and forget in a relationship." Etc.

"I'll let this slide this once, but it better not happen again!". Shortened, still means this very thing. She thinks because she didn't leave me right then, she forgave me.
But it's still apart of "everything combined". She was serious to me in her responses.

It took me telling me it was over for 1st a single incident. Then it was, that was the last straw. Then it was, everything combined. And I asked her, does that sound like she's ever forgiven me? She said she's let this slide, that slide, all these thing slide...

I think I have switched from severe anger and heartbreak, to simply heartbreak, and weight lifting off of me.
My eyes have finally opened to the emotional abuse I have endured for 14 years.
And because I'm so trusting that those "I love" care about me, I just never saw it.

#ADHD

I say yes.
"Are you sure? Are you sure you can do this?"

#ADHD

And 9 out of 10 fucking times I am ACCUSED of making whoever feel stupid...
How is it my fault you feel stupid? How!? I didn't do anything "extra and out of the way" to make you feel that way. But that's my fault too.

AND I DON'T CARE IF PEOPLE DON'T "LIKE" BEING TOLD THAT I KNOW MORE ABOUT "MY FUCKING DISORDER" THAN THEY DO! I don't care if they don't "like" being told that, that advice, is not helpful to me, this is what is. You're insecurities aren't my issue.

So it's appropriate that I accommodate someone in a wheelchair. Or a debilitating disease. Chronic illness what have you. But when I ask for the same care for my disability, I may as well not have one.

When I am explaining my disability to you. It is NOT appropriate for you to question me or my motives.
Unless those questions are about my disability. 
#ADHD
Do you think I'm simply making excuses? Do you think I'm lying? I'm stupid? What!? Why is everyone else's issues important? But my disability is "no big deal, you just need to DO it."...

And when someone tells me that "You just need to do it, it's that simple!" And I say in return to you that, "I can't just do it like that, my brain doesn't work that way."
What do you think I mean, or am doing?
I have been treated badly by the people who love me. I deserve to be believed when I say something negatively effects me, without being treated as if I am accusing them of abusing me.

And when I say that I want to go to marriage counseling. She asked if I could sit, and let he speak. I said yes, of course. "Are you sure?" "Are you absolutely sure you can do that without getting defensive?". And I fucking lost it.

My mother was in a sever car accident in HS. After that she had anger issues. Comparing this to my disability is frankly insulting to my disability. And for people who I should be able to trust to treat me that way...
I just don't know anymore.

And it's not just her! Sure she raised me, she is mother. She knows me very well. But to think that she knows MY MENTAL ILLNESS better, or AS WELL AS ME!? No. I live with this disability. She even compared her brain dmg anger issues to my blow ups.

She tells me that I NEED to understand that no one likes to be told that sort of thing. Asked if I was sure if someone interacting differently with me would work. As if I don't know my disability. And then GOT angry when I told her she doesn't know it as I do. That's fair to me?
I don't fucking deserve this! I don't deserve this at all! My own fucking mother!

You're bothered by how I act. I tell you what causes me to act that way, assure you I'm not attacking you. Assure that you don't mean to. But I'M the one that NEEDS to understand. What I do effects you negatively, so who cares how you treat me? My whole fucking life!

And by me explaining how these interactions effect me to people, I am literally asking you to understand my disability and to afford me an accommodation on how you treat me. That's a fair trade isn't it? How am I asking too much?

And for people to attack me about my behavior, want me to change the way I act, and then are NOT WILLING TO LISTEN OR BELIEVE ME WHEN I AM GIVING THEM THE FUCKING KEY TO CASTLE! I am trying to ask you to change the ways you interact with me to make that change.
It doesn't matter that I'm bothered, and that it triggers my disability. The ONLY THING THAT MATTERS TO OTHER PEOPLE IS THAT INTERACTING WITH ME "EFFECTS" THEM, AND NOTHING TO HOW IT EFFECTS ME!

Even if that is the opening line. When I try to explain to people that the ways they interact with me, are harmful to me, they ALWAYS act as if I'm the bad guy. As if I should just perceive what they mean, and NOT BE BOTHERED BY IT!

Because it's inconvenient to THEM that I'm saying they misunderstood what I meant? Why is that a fair reaction when I am TRYING to explain my disability and how it effects me? And it doesn't matter if I start by saying that it is NOT an attack on them

When I try to explain my disability to people, unless they're already understanding of it, or live with it, it ALWAYS THE SAME THING!
"Well that may be, but YOU need to understand that people perceive that this way, no one likes to be told they didn't understand."
SO WHAT!?

Worst part about ADHD is that everyone enforces that you're a piece of shit.
I'M EXPECTED TO UNDERSTAND AND BE SENSITIVE TO EVERYONE ELSE'S FEELINGS AND PERCEPTIONS OF THE THINGS THEY MEAN, BUT I'M NOT ALLOWED TO BE UNDERSTOOD!
EVERYONE KNOWS MY DISABILITY MORE THAN ME!
